70@@fprintf stderr "Usage: loopback_test TEST [SIZE] ITERATIONS [SYSPATH] [DBGPATH]

" "  Run TEST for a number of ITERATIONS with operation data SIZE bytes
" "  TEST may be 'ping' 'transfer' or 'sink'
" "  SIZE indicates the size of transfer <= greybus max payload bytes
" "  ITERATIONS indicates the number of times to execute TEST at SIZE bytes
" "             Note if ITERATIONS is set to zero then this utility will
" "             initiate an infinite (non terminating) test and exit
" "             without logging any metrics data
" "  SYSPATH indicates the sysfs path for the loopback greybus entries e.g.
" "          /sys/bus/greybus/devices
" "  DBGPATH indicates the debugfs path for the loopback greybus entries e.g.
" "          /sys/kernel/debug/gb_loopback/
" " Mandatory arguments
" "   -t     must be one of the test names - sink, transfer or ping
" "   -i     iteration count - the number of iterations to run the test over
" " Optional arguments
" "   -S     sysfs location - location for greybus 'endo' entires default /sys/bus/greybus/devices/
" "   -D     debugfs location - location for loopback debugfs entries default /sys/kernel/debug/gb_loopback/
" "   -s     size of data packet to send during test - defaults to zero
" "   -m     mask - a bit mask of connections to include example: -m 8 = 4th connection -m 9 = 1st and 4th connection etc
" "                 default is zero which means broadcast to all connections
" "   -v     verbose output
" "   -d     debug output
" "   -r     raw data output - when specified the full list of latency values are included in the output CSV
" "   -p     porcelain - when specified printout is in a user-friendly non-CSV format. This option suppresses writing to CSV file
" "   -a     aggregate - show aggregation of all enabled devices
" "   -l     list found loopback devices and exit
" "   -x     Async - Enable async transfers
" "   -o     Async Timeout - Timeout in uSec for async operations
" "   -c     Max number of outstanding operations for async operations
" "   -w     Wait in uSec between operations
" "Examples:
" "  Send 10000 transfers with a packet size of 128 bytes to all active connections
" "  loopback_test -t transfer -s 128 -i 10000 -S /sys/bus/greybus/devices/ -D /sys/kernel/debug/gb_loopback/
" "  loopback_test -t transfer -s 128 -i 10000 -m 0
" "  Send 10000 transfers with a packet size of 128 bytes to connection 1 and 4
" "  loopback_test -t transfer -s 128 -i 10000 -m 9
" "  loopback_test -t ping -s 0 128 -i -S /sys/bus/greybus/devices/ -D /sys/kernel/debug/gb_loopback/
" "  loopback_test -t sink -s 2030 -i 32768 -S /sys/bus/greybus/devices/ -D /sys/kernel/debug/gb_loopback/
"
